    history: 'Peridot is one of the oldest gemstones in human history, with mining on the Egyptian island of Zabargad (also called St. John\'s Island or Topazios) dating back to at least 1500 BCE. Ancient Egyptians called it the gem of the sun and mined it exclusively for their pharaohs — a peridot mine on Zabargad was a state secret [Kunz, G.F., 1913. The Curious Lore of Precious Stones]. Many of Cleopatra\'s famous emeralds may actually have been peridot — ancient sources frequently confused the two green stones. Peridot was used extensively in medieval European church treasury: gems in the reliquary of the Three Kings in Cologne Cathedral, previously labeled emeralds, were recently identified as peridot.',
